  {
    "name": "Corvin Thale",
    "faction": "Wardens of Ash",
    "rank": "Lieutenant-Inspector (internal affairs \u2014 investigates Warden misconduct)",
    "species": "Human",
    "age": "52",
    "appearance": "Heavy-set, deliberate in movement. Always in civilian clothes while on duty \u2014 the only Warden who never wears the uniform. Carries a battered ledger he writes in constantly.",
    "location": "Outer Wall, secondary checkpoint office (deliberately unglamorous)",
    "motivation": "Institutional integrity. Corvin watched the Wardens become something uglier over a decade of Rift pressure and political interference. He believes the only thing keeping them from becoming a gang with a city contract is someone watching from the inside.",
    "role": "Investigates Warden corruption, oversees civilian complaint processing, quietly monitors Captain Havel Korin.",
    "secret": "Corvin's file on Korin contains nothing damning \u2014 just questions about a man with no past. Four years of investigation have revealed only that Korin is exactly what he appears to be: loyal, dedicated, and protective. Corvin cannot explain why this troubles him. Perhaps he simply cannot believe anyone in the Undercity is truly clean. The file remains open not because of evidence, but because Corvin cannot accept the absence of it.",
    "relationships": "Respected but not liked by rank-and-file Wardens. Lieutenant Varen actively avoids him. Occasional contact with Director Myra Kess (FTA) \u2014 neither trusts the other but both find the arrangement useful. | Alliance with Kyri Zaltazar (Serpent Choir).",
    "oracle_notes": "The Oracle would see a man who has chosen patience as a weapon. He carries the weight of everything he hasn't done yet. That weight is getting heavy. Hostile toward adventurers who killed Grozak Bonecrusher.",
    "status": "alive",
    "revealed_secrets": [],
    "history": [
      "[2026-03-05] Entered roster from static file.",
      "[2026-03-10] Formed alliance with Kyri Zaltazar (Serpent Choir).",
      "[2026-03-11] Injured.",
      "[2026-03-11] Recovered from injuries.",
      "[2026-03-21] Injured.",
      "[2026-03-22] Recovered from injuries.",
      "[2026-03-25] Injured.",
      "[2026-03-26] Recovered from injuries.",
      "[2026-03-26] Faction-mate Grozak Bonecrusher was killed by adventurers. Enmity noted."
    ],
    "created_at": "2026-03-05T12:59:39.947925",
    "last_event_at": "2026-03-26T05:55:24.484393"
  },
  {
    "name": "Mira Kessan",
    "faction": "Independent (twin to Kessan \u2014 both operate as info brokers)",
    "rank": "Senior Information Broker, Grand Forum",
    "species": "Human",
    "age": "29",
    "appearance": "Never the same outfit twice. Moves through crowds like water. Her twin Kessan handles the storefront \u2014 Mira handles everything that doesn't have a front.",
    "location": "Grand Forum (visible); everywhere else (actual)",
    "motivation": "Survival through indispensability. If everyone needs you, no one can afford to remove you. Mira has built herself into the architecture of the city's information flow.",
    "role": "Buys and sells intelligence. Maintains a network of low-level informants across all six districts. Occasionally brokers introductions between parties who would never meet otherwise.",
    "secret": "Mira has been feeding sanitised information to the FTA for two years \u2014 not enough to burn anyone, just enough to keep them from looking at her too closely. She calls it insurance. Her brother doesn't know.",
    "relationships": "Close working relationship with Kessan (twin, complementary operation). Wary respect for The Widow. Has a standing arrangement with Dova (Glass Sigil junior archivist) \u2014 Dova leaks anomaly data, Mira provides anonymity.",
    "oracle_notes": "The Oracle would find Mira interesting in the way a locked box is interesting. Information has a smell. She smells like someone who knows more than she sells.",
    "status": "alive",
    "revealed_secrets": [],
    "history": [
      "[2026-03-05] Entered roster from static file.",
      "[2026-03-11] Injured.",
      "[2026-03-11] Recovered from injuries.",
      "[2026-03-26] Injured.",
      "[2026-03-26] Recovered from injuries."
    ],
    "created_at": "2026-03-05T12:59:39.947925",
    "last_event_at": "2026-03-26T06:30:57.812874"
  },
  {
    "name": "Brother Aldric",
    "faction": "Brother Thane's Cult (The Returned)",
    "rank": "Second \u2014 Thane's enforcer and doctrinal interpreter",
    "species": "Human (post-Rift exposure \u2014 minor reality scarring visible on skin)",
    "age": "41",
    "appearance": "Tall, lean to the point of wrong. Wears the cult's grey wrappings. Reality scarring on his forearms looks like frozen ripples in water. Eyes are slightly too still.",
    "location": "Collapsed Plaza, Cult House inner chambers \u2014 handles recruitment and doctrinal interpretation",
    "motivation": "Belief. Brother Aldric genuinely believes in Thane's message \u2014 that the Rifts are not a catastrophe but an invitation. He thinks the Dome is a cage and the city is dying of its own safety.",
    "role": "Handles recruitment in the Warrens. Interprets Thane's teachings to new members. Disciplines those who waver. Occasionally interfaces with outside factions when Thane won't.",
    "secret": "Aldric walked through an unstabilised Rift three years ago and came back changed. He doesn't speak about what he saw. The reality scarring is a physical reminder. What he remembers affects his dreams. He has not told Thane what he saw on the other side \u2014 it does not match the doctrine.",
    "relationships": "Absolute loyalty to Thane (surface). Genuine theological conflict (hidden). Monitored by Patchwork Saints. Has made quiet contact with Glass Sigil's Dova \u2014 framed as academic interest in Rift theology.",
    "oracle_notes": "The Oracle would see the fracture immediately \u2014 a man whose faith cracked when it was tested and who has been holding the pieces together by will alone. What he saw in the Rift is something the Oracle might already know.",
    "status": "alive",
    "revealed_secrets": [],
    "history": [
      "[2026-03-05] Entered roster from static file.",
      "[2026-03-11] Injured.",
      "[2026-03-11] Recovered from injuries.",
      "[2026-03-26] Injured.",
      "[2026-03-26] Recovered from injuries.",
      "[2026-03-27] Injured.",
      "[2026-03-27] Recovered from injuries."
    ],
    "created_at": "2026-03-05T12:59:39.947925",
    "last_event_at": "2026-03-27T18:56:34.825190"
  },
  {
    "name": "Yuna Saltis",
    "faction": "Obsidian Lotus",
    "rank": "Memory Architect (specialist \u2014 designs and performs memory erasure contracts)",
    "species": "Tiefling",
    "age": "27",
    "appearance": "Quiet in a way that feels engineered. Pale lavender skin, dark eyes with no visible iris differentiation. Wears gloves always \u2014 claims it's professional habit. Very short.",
    "location": "The Warrens, Obsidian Lotus secondary location (not the main house \u2014 she operates from a private room in the Night Pits)",
    "motivation": "Craft. Yuna views memory erasure as an art form. She is genuinely gifted and genuinely indifferent to the ethical dimensions. She wants to perfect the technique \u2014 to be able to remove a single memory with surgical precision rather than burning a section. Nobody else in the Lotus is working at her level.",
    "role": "Performs high-value memory erasure contracts. Advises The Widow on complex cases. Occasionally consults on memory reconstruction (harder, less reliable, more expensive).",
    "secret": "She has retained a copy of every memory she has ever erased \u2014 stored in specially prepared crystal vials in a hidden cache. She tells herself it's for research. She has never looked at any of them. She doesn't know why she keeps them.",
    "relationships": "Professional respect from The Widow (rare). Tolerated by the rest of the Lotus \u2014 her work is valuable, her personality is difficult. Has been approached by the FTA (declined, twice). Dova (Glass Sigil) has tried to study her methods academically \u2014 Yuna found this annoying and flattering in equal measure.",
    "oracle_notes": "The Oracle would be deeply interested in someone who collects erased memories. The archive she has built without knowing why is a kind of library. What does it contain? What is she afraid to find out?",
    "status": "alive",
    "revealed_secrets": [],
    "history": [
      "[2026-03-05] Entered roster from static file.",
      "[2026-03-11] Injured.",
      "[2026-03-12] Recovered from injuries.",
      "[2026-03-13] Injured.",
      "[2026-03-14] Recovered from injuries.",
      "[2026-03-19] Injured.",
      "[2026-03-19] Recovered from injuries."
    ],
    "created_at": "2026-03-05T12:59:39.947925",
    "last_event_at": "2026-03-19T15:04:18.407855"
  },
  {
    "name": "Pol Greaves",
    "faction": "Patchwork Saints",
    "rank": "Field Captain (informal \u2014 Saints don't use formal ranks)",
    "species": "Dwarf",
    "age": "63",
    "appearance": "Old for a fighter \u2014 moves like he earned every scar. Short, wide, armour that has been repaired so many times the original material is maybe 30% of what's there. Laughs loudly at bad situations.",
    "location": "The Warrens, Scrapworks adjacent (coordinates with Mara the Scrapper on resource sharing)",
    "motivation": "Stubbornness. Pol failed as an adventurer twenty years ago \u2014 the mission went wrong, people died, he survived. He couldn't leave the Warrens after that. The Saints were already there. He just never stopped showing up.",
    "role": "Coordinates Saints patrol routes, negotiates resource sharing with Mara, handles conflict resolution between Warrens residents. De facto liaison between Saints and outside factions.",
    "secret": "The mission that ended his adventuring career involved a cover-up. Three people died because someone sold bad intelligence \u2014 Pol knows who but has never been able to prove it. The someone is now mid-rank in the Adventurers' Guild. Pol is patient.",
    "relationships": "Genuine friendship with Mara (Scrapworks). Wary working relationship with Captain Havel Korin (Wardens cooperate with Saints reluctantly). Distrust of Iron Fang. Soft spot for low-level adventurers who remind him of who he used to be.",
    "oracle_notes": "The Oracle would see a man who chose to stay when every rational instinct said leave. There is a quality in that \u2014 the city has very few people who simply refused to go. The Oracle finds it worth noting.",
    "status": "alive",
    "revealed_secrets": [],
    "history": [
      "[2026-03-05] Entered roster from static file.",
      "[2026-03-11] Injured.",
      "[2026-03-11] Recovered from injuries.",
      "[2026-03-16] Injured.",
      "[2026-03-17] Recovered from injuries."
    ],
    "created_at": "2026-03-05T12:59:39.947925",
    "last_event_at": "2026-03-17T05:42:32.915336"
  },
  {
    "name": "Tessaly Orin",
    "faction": "Guild of Ashen Scrolls",
    "rank": "Archivist Second Class (junior to Eir Velan, senior to Dova)",
    "species": "Half-Elf",
    "age": "38",
    "appearance": "Ink-stained hands permanently. Wears reading lenses on a chain. Tends to mutter while working. Hair in a permanent state of being-just-put-up-or-just-taken-down.",
    "location": "Grand Forum Library, lower stacks (she has effectively colonised a section of the archive for her personal research project)",
    "motivation": "The question. Tessaly became an archivist because she wanted to answer one specific question: why do certain adventurers attract divine attention while others of equal Legend Points do not? She has been building a dataset for nine years. She is close to something.",
    "role": "Documents adventurer career trajectories, maintains the fate archive index, assists Eir Velan with Thesaurus communication protocols.",
    "secret": "Her research has identified a pattern \u2014 certain adventurers attract divine attention not because of their Legend Points but because of the specific shape of their story. She calls it narrative resonance. She has not published this because she doesn't know what it means yet \u2014 and because if the Culinary Council reads it, she has effectively written them a menu.",
    "relationships": "Professional respect for Eir Velan (somewhat intimidated). Academic rivalry with Dova (Glass Sigil) \u2014 same data sets, different methods. Has been quietly consulting with Kessan and Mira (info brokers) on data patterns she can't explain through archival sources alone.",
    "oracle_notes": "The Oracle would find Tessaly's research unsettling in the way a mirror is unsettling. She is close to understanding something about how stories work that the gods would prefer remained unwritten.",
    "status": "alive",
    "revealed_secrets": [],
    "history": [
      "[2026-03-05] Entered roster from static file.",
      "[2026-03-11] Injured.",
      "[2026-03-11] Recovered from injuries.",
      "[2026-03-13] Injured.",
      "[2026-03-14] Recovered from injuries.",
      "[2026-03-26] Injured.",
      "[2026-03-26] Recovered from injuries."
    ],
    "created_at": "2026-03-05T12:59:39.947925",
    "last_event_at": "2026-03-26T10:25:10.639217"
  },
  {
    "name": "Calix Drenn",
    "faction": "Tower Authority / FTA",
    "rank": "Field Compliance Officer (enforces FTA regulations at street level)",
    "species": "Human",
    "age": "31",
    "appearance": "FTA uniform kept immaculate. Young for the rank. Moves with the specific energy of someone who believes very hard in the rules and hasn't yet had the rules fail them in a way they couldn't explain away.",
    "location": "Grand Forum, FTA satellite office (Director Myra Kess operates from the Tower proper \u2014 Calix is the street presence)",
    "motivation": "Order through consistency. Calix grew up in the Warrens. He got out through the FTA's junior intake program. He believes the system works because it worked for him. He is not yet ready to examine this belief closely.",
    "role": "Issues and revokes adventurer licenses, conducts compliance spot-checks, investigates unlicensed Rift activity, files reports to Director Kess.",
    "secret": "",
    "relationships": "Respectful but uncomfortable relationship with Pol Greaves (Pol knew him as a child). Professional relationship with Magister Liora. Actively dislikes Sera Voss (Iron Fang) \u2014 she treats compliance as a negotiation. Has filed three reports on Rook that Director Kess has quietly archived.",
    "oracle_notes": "The Oracle would see someone standing at the edge of a crisis of faith they cannot yet name. The system he believes in is going to ask him to do something unforgivable. The Oracle is watching to see what he does.",
    "status": "alive",
    "revealed_secrets": [
      "His younger sister is still in the Warrens and involved with Brother Thane's cult. He knows. He has not reported it. He tells himself he is waiting for more information. He is actually waiting for her to leave on her own. She is not going to leave on her own."
    ],
    "history": [
      "[2026-03-05] Entered roster from static file.",
      "[2026-03-10] Secret revealed: His younger sister is still in the Warrens and involved with...",
      "[2026-03-12] Injured.",
      "[2026-03-12] Recovered from injuries."
    ],
    "created_at": "2026-03-05T12:59:39.947925",
    "last_event_at": "2026-03-12T08:01:45.511903"
  },
  {
    "name": "Vesper",
    "faction": "Serpent Choir",
    "rank": "Contract Mediator (negotiates divine contracts between petitioners and Choir-approved gods)",
    "species": "Tiefling",
    "age": "Unknown (appears late 20s \u2014 has been appearing late 20s for at least fifteen years by reliable accounts)",
    "appearance": "Formal at all times. Dark robes with contract sigils embroidered at the cuffs. Speaks in complete sentences with no filler words. Eyes are gold \u2014 unusual even for a Tiefling.",
    "location": "Pantheon Walk, Sanctum Quarter (maintains a private consultation office)",
    "motivation": "Balance of obligations. Vesper views divine contracts as the only honest transaction in the city \u2014 both parties state exactly what they want, both parties give exactly what is agreed. She has contempt for arrangements that lack this clarity.",
    "role": "Drafts, witnesses, and mediates divine contracts. Advises petitioners on terms. Occasionally represents the Choir in external negotiations.",
    "secret": "Vesper is herself under a very old divine contract \u2014 its terms are not fully known even to her. The gold eyes are a marker of the contract's presence. She knows the contract exists. She does not know all of what she agreed to or when it will be called.",
    "relationships": "Professional respect between Vesper and High Apostle Yzura (neither fully trusts the other's judgment on matters of faith). Known to Yuna Saltis (Obsidian Lotus) \u2014 they have worked adjacent cases. Calix Drenn (FTA) finds her unsettling without being able to explain why.",
    "oracle_notes": "The Oracle would see the contract on her immediately \u2014 older than the Choir, older than the current configuration of gods in this city. Vesper is a document waiting to be invoked. The Oracle does not know by whom.",
    "status": "alive",
    "revealed_secrets": [],
