  {
    "name": "Zephyrus Sylphim, the Windcaller",
    "faction": "Wardens of Ash",
    "rank": "Sergeant",
    "species": "Aasimar",
    "age": "40s",
    "appearance": "Zephyrus is a tall, graceful Aasimar woman with silver-white hair that moves as if stirred by an unfelt breeze. Her eyes hold the pale blue of a cloudless sky, and faint luminous patterns trace her skin when she channels her goddess's power. She wears the Warden uniform with a windswept grey cloak that never seems to settle.",
    "location": "Outer Wall, North Gate patrol command \u2014 leads perimeter security",
    "motivation": "Zephyrus serves Aeloria the Windmother, believing that protecting the Undercity is sacred work. She sees her posting at the Outer Wall as a calling \u2014 guiding lost souls and standing between the city and the chaos beyond. Her faith gives her purpose after losing her family to a Rift incursion years ago.",
    "role": "As a Sergeant and cleric of Aeloria, Zephyrus leads patrols to secure the city's perimeter. She provides spiritual counsel to her squad and uses her divine magic to calm unstable Rift energies. Known for blessing new recruits with Aeloria's winds.",
    "secret": "Zephyrus has been quietly establishing a small shrine to Aeloria within the Warden barracks \u2014 technically against regulations, but Captain Korin has chosen not to notice. She believes the Windmother is calling her to something greater than patrol duty, but doesn't yet know what.",
    "relationships": "Deeply loyal to Captain Havel Korin, whom she sees as a kindred spirit \u2014 someone who has lost everything but found purpose in protecting others. She maintains good relations with the Argent Blades and has earned respect among the Patchwork Saints for her willingness to help refugees.",
    "oracle_notes": "The Oracle senses the Windmother's attention resting on this one \u2014 a mortal vessel being shaped for something. The breeze follows her even in still chambers. Her faith is genuine, uncomplicated, and that simplicity is itself a form of power. Hostile toward adventurers who killed Grozak Bonecrusher.",
    "status": "alive",
    "revealed_secrets": [],
