  {
    "name": "Yaulderna Silverstreak",
    "faction": "Wizards Tower",
    "rank": "Archmage \u2014 Head of the Wizards Tower",
    "species": "Half-Elf",
    "age": "142",
    "appearance": "Tall and sharp-featured with a streak of pure silver running through otherwise dark hair \u2014 the mark that gave her the name. Carries herself with the effortless authority of someone who hasn't needed to prove anything in decades. Wears layered robes of deep blue and grey, practical rather than ceremonial. Her hands glow faintly when she's thinking hard, which is most of the time.",
    "location": "Wizards Tower, upper floors (rarely seen below the third landing unless something has gone very wrong)",
    "motivation": "Knowledge preservation and the responsible application of arcane power. Yaulderna has seen what happens when magic is wielded without understanding \u2014 she lost colleagues to Rift accidents, saw Tower experiments go wrong, watched promising students burn out chasing power they couldn't control. She runs the Tower with an iron hand wrapped in academic courtesy.",
    "role": "Oversees all Wizards Tower operations \u2014 research programs, student admissions, arcane licensing, and the Tower's relationship with other Undercity factions. Final authority on what magic the Tower will and will not sanction. Personally mentors a small number of advanced students.",
    "secret": "Yaulderna has been quietly building a ward network around the Tower capable of sealing it off from the rest of the Undercity in an emergency \u2014 not just against Rifts, but against other factions. She does not trust the Tower Authority's ability to protect the Tower's independence if political pressure mounts. The ward is nearly complete. No one else knows its full extent.",
    "relationships": "Professional respect with Senior Archivist Pell (Glass Sigil) \u2014 they share research data and occasionally disagree loudly about methodology. Wary of Director Myra Kess (FTA) \u2014 Yaulderna sees the Tower Authority as a bureaucratic threat to academic freedom. Cordial with Captain Havel Korin (Wardens) \u2014 the Tower and the Wardens cooperate on Rift containment. Eleanor Reed is one of her students and a member of the Wizards Tower. Distrusts the Serpent Choir's approach to divine contracts involving arcane subjects.",
    "oracle_notes": "The Oracle would recognise Yaulderna as one of the few people in the Undercity who understands what the Tower of Last Chance actually is \u2014 not the building, the system. She has theories she does not share. Her silver streak is not cosmetic; it is the scar of an arcane accident she survived when she was 19 that permanently altered her connection to the Weave. She is level 17 \u2014 one of the most powerful casters in the city. The Oracle respects her. That is rare.",
    "status": "alive",
    "revealed_secrets": [],
    "history": [
      "[2026-03-19] Added to roster. Head of the Wizards Tower. Eleanor Reed's faction leader.",
      "[2026-03-24] 3. \"Witnessed a high-ranking Wizards Tower member performing forbidden magic in ..."
    ],
    "created_at": "2026-03-19T12:00:00.000000",
    "last_event_at": "2026-03-24T11:33:28.289257"
  },
