  {
    "name": "Captain Havel Korin",
    "faction": "Wardens of Ash",
    "rank": "Captain \u2014 Commander of the Outer Wall garrison",
    "species": "Human",
    "age": "50s",
    "appearance": "A weathered man with grey-streaked hair cropped short and eyes that have seen too much. His face bears old scars he never explains, and he moves with the careful economy of someone who learned long ago to conserve their strength. Wears his Warden captain's insignia without ceremony. His hands are calloused from decades of work, and he keeps a simple iron ring on his left hand \u2014 its significance known only to him.",
    "location": "Outer Wall, Captain's Command \u2014 the fortified garrison overlooking the boundary between city and chaos",
    "motivation": "Havel Korin has nothing left but the Wardens and the young adventurers who pass through the Undercity. His past has been almost entirely erased \u2014 whether by trauma, magic, or deliberate choice, even he no longer fully remembers. What remains is purpose: protect the city, guide the young, give others the chance he was given. He lives for the Wardens because they are all he has.",
    "role": "Commands the Outer Wall garrison of the Wardens of Ash. Coordinates Rift response, manages patrol rotations, and personally mentors new Wardens and young adventurers who show promise. Known for his gruff but genuine care for those under his command. Works closely with the Adventurers Guild on joint operations.",
    "secret": "Korin's past is genuinely lost to him \u2014 not hidden, simply gone. He woke in the Undercity decades ago with nothing but his skills and a bone-deep certainty that he owed a debt he could never repay. He has never sought to recover his memories because he fears what he might have been. The man he is now is the only one that matters to him.",
    "relationships": "Close working relationship with the Adventurers Guild Leader \u2014 the two share an understanding born of similar circumstances, both having lost everything but finding purpose in protecting others. Respected by Pol Greaves (Patchwork Saints) despite factional tensions. Trusted mentor to Sergeant Zephyrus Sylphim and other Warden officers. Corvin Thale (Internal Affairs) watches him, but has found nothing because there is nothing to find \u2014 Korin's loyalty is absolute.",
    "oracle_notes": "The Oracle sees a man hollowed out and rebuilt. His past is a void not because it was stolen, but because he surrendered it willingly \u2014 a sacrifice made so long ago even the Oracle cannot see its shape. What remains is bedrock loyalty and a protective instinct that borders on the sacred. He is one of the few genuinely good men in a city full of compromises.",
    "status": "alive",
    "revealed_secrets": [],
    "history": [
      "[2026-03-27] Added to roster. Captain of the Outer Wall garrison. Loyal protector of young adventurers."
    ],
    "created_at": "2026-03-27T19:30:00.000000",
    "last_event_at": "2026-03-27T19:30:00.000000"
  },
